1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,585
<i>You were my first, Alice.</i>

2
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:05,380
<i>My first one that got away.</i>

3
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:08,717
<i>Stay away from me!</i>

4
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:10,719
<i>Mel, I'm following a trail of blood</i>

5
00:00:10,802 --> 00:00:12,011
<i>But if they're injured,</i>

6
00:00:12,095 --> 00:00:13,930
<i>why are they heading this way?</i>

7
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,849
<i>I can't… this is just like that night.</i>

8
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:17,726
<i>That night, Louisa was murdered.</i>

9
00:00:17,809 --> 00:00:19,394
<i>This is different. It's not the same.</i>

10
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:20,770
<i>This is all your fault!</i>

11
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,398
<i>You should be minding your own business!</i>

12
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:26,443
- [screaming]
- [grunts]

13
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,611
<i>You're murdered Louisa, right?</i>

14
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:31,406
- <i>Why did you do that?</i>
- <i>Did she find out too?</i>

15
00:00:31,489 --> 00:00:34,409
<i>Your friend doesn't mind her own business.</i>

16
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:36,161
<i>Liezel, I thought you loved me?</i>

17
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:37,871
- <i>You flirt!</i>
- [Louisa] <i>Uncle?</i>

18
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:39,748
[girl crying] <i>Help me!</i>

19
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,041
[Edward] <i>Don't make any noise.</i>

20
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:46,880
[dramatic music playing]

21
00:00:52,302 --> 00:00:53,553
Ah, Uncle, um…

22
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:58,933
No one was answering
the door, so I… I let myself in.

23
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:01,519
I'm actually here
to get the money I was to borrow.

24
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:03,772
[dramatic music continues]

25
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:05,482
[breathes shakily]

26
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:06,775
Ah…

27
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,568
Uncle the…

28
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:12,113
the truth is, I'm actually leaving Amurao.

29
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:15,700
But don't worry, I'll slowly pay you back!

30
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,203
- [sighs]
- [thunder rumbles]

31
00:01:18,828 --> 00:01:20,705
[Edward] I can't blame you, Louisa.

32
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:23,041
The people in Amurao
are exhausting to deal with.

33
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:26,753
You have to keep smiling,
even though you really want to…

34
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:28,963
kill them.

35
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,549
But I don't want
to do that to you, Louisa.

36
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:34,135
You're my niece's friend.

37
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:36,346
Alice is special to me.

38
00:01:37,388 --> 00:01:38,973
And you're different
from the people around here.

39
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:43,978
[dramatic music crescendos]

40
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:46,481
- What a shame.
- [breathing heavily]

41
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:48,358
Auntie! Auntie!

42
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:50,193
- She can't hear you.
- [thunder rumbles]

43
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:55,365
[dramatic music resumes]

44
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,867
[tense music sting]

45
00:01:57,951 --> 00:02:00,453
Aah! Let me go!

46
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:03,957
Please, I won't talk! I'll leave Amurao!

47
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,626
- I won't tell anyone!
- [grunts]

48
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:10,213
- [coughs]
- [grunting]

49
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:13,091
- [gasping]
- [grunts]

50
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:15,552
- [grunts]
- [groans]

51
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:20,723
[suspenseful music playing]

52
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:28,648
[both grunting]

53
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,109
What were you doing to that child?!

54
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:33,570
What were you doing?!
We treated you like a father!

55
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,655
You're a demon! A demon!

56
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:37,991
[both grunting]

57
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,745
Let me go!

58
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,128
- Let me go!
- [kicks landing, grunts]

59
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:54,173
[groans]

60
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,596
Let me go!

61
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:03,516
It hurts! Let me go!

62
00:03:04,684 --> 00:03:06,352
- [grunts]
- [thuds]

63
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:12,775
- [stirring music playing]
- [thunder rumbles]

64
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:16,446
[water running]

65
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:20,658
[stirring music continues]

66
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,579
[grunts softly]

67
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:35,006
- [thunder rumbles]
- [stirring music intensifies]

68
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:40,053
[suspenseful music playing]

69
00:03:40,136 --> 00:03:46,226
[grunts, breathing heavily]

70
00:03:46,976 --> 00:03:48,228
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

71
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:50,897
Help me!

72
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,734
- [groans, kicks landing]
- [music becomes dramatic]

73
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,905
- [thunder rumbles]
- [breathing heavily]

74
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:03,910
Help me! Someone please help me!

75
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:09,374
- [breathing heavily]
- [dramatic music continues]

76
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:10,667
Help me!

77
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,295
[groans]

78
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:16,923
Help me!

79
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:20,760
Help…

80
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:24,806
H- help me, please!

81
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:31,479
[music becomes ominous]

82
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:42,782
[zips]

83
00:04:44,158 --> 00:04:46,035
[thunder rumbles]

84
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:51,165
[ominous music continues]

85
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:52,333
[thunder rumbles]

86
00:04:53,918 --> 00:05:00,425
[theme music playing]

87
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:10,995
[young Beth] <i>Louisa! Where are you?!</i>

88
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:12,371
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa!</i>

89
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:14,874
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa?</i>

90
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:16,459
- [whimpers]
<i>- Louisa!</i>

91
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:17,418
[Edward] <i>Psst!</i>

92
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:18,544
[thunder roaring]

93
00:06:18,628 --> 00:06:22,840
- [gasping, sobbing]
- [dramatic music playing]

94
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:28,346
<i>- Help! Ah!</i>
- [rattling]

95
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:31,140
<i>Help! Let me go! You're a demon!</i>

96
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:32,892
<i>You're disgusting!</i>

97
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,268
- [blow lands]
- [both grunt]

98
00:06:34,352 --> 00:06:36,145
- [breathes sharply]
- [Edward grunts]

99
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:40,191
[dramatic music continues]

100
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:43,402
[grunting weakly, breathing sharply]

101
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:46,906
[dramatic music continues]

102
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,032
[sniffling]

103
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,575
<i>No.</i> [sobs, whimpers]

104
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:53,704
[sniffles, sobs]

105
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:56,415
<i>- Louisa!</i>
- [thunder roars]

106
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,209
[young Louisa] <i>Help!</i>

107
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:00,086
<i>Help me!</i>

108
00:07:00,419 --> 00:07:01,629
<i>Did you hear that?</i>

109
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:03,172
<i>There!</i>

110
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,298
<i>- Louisa!</i>
- [thunder claps]

111
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:05,925
[sobs shakily]

112
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:08,344
- [dramatic music ends]
- [thunder rumbles]

113
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,012
- [sobs loudly]
- [grunts]

114
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,639
<i>No!</i>

115
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,474
<i>- No!</i>
- [flesh tears]

116
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:14,976
[ominous music playing]

117
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:17,353
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa!</i>

118
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:19,105
[young Beth panting]

119
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:21,524
<i>- Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa!</i> [sobs loudly]

120
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:23,359
<i>- Louisa! Louisa!</i>
<i>- Louisa, wake up!</i>

121
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,944
<i>- Argh!</i>
- [Mel sobs] <i>Louisa!</i>

122
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,070
- [young Beth] <i>Louisa!</i>
- [blows landing]

123
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,281
- [Edward grunting]
- [girls sobbing] <i>Louisa!</i>

124
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:31,617
- [young Erica<i></i>grunts]
- [Edward grunts]

125
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:33,870
- [young Mel] <i>You killed her!</i>
- [young Erica] <i>You monster!</i>

126
00:07:33,953 --> 00:07:35,037
[Edward grunts, screams]

127
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:36,456
[girls grunt, gasp]

128
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,166
- [young Erica] <i>Mel!</i>
- [Edward grunts]

129
00:07:38,249 --> 00:07:40,209
<i>- You're evil!</i>
- [young Beth] <i>Louisa! Louisa!</i>

130
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,003
- [young Mel] <i>Louisa!</i> [sobs]
- [both grunt]

131
00:07:42,086 --> 00:07:43,796
<i>- Louisa!</i>
- [gasps loudly]

132
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,006
- [Edward gasps]
- [tense music sting]

133
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,133
<i>You monster!</i>

134
00:07:47,216 --> 00:07:49,552
- [young Beth]<i> Louisa!</i>
- [girls sobbing]

135
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:51,053
<i>- Louisa! Louisa!</i>
- [sobbing continues]

136
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:53,598
[all sobbing] <i>Louisa!</i>

137
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:55,349
<i>Louisa! Help!</i>

138
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:58,144
- [sobbing continues]
<i>- Louisa!</i>

139
00:07:58,227 --> 00:08:00,062
[unsettling music playing]

140
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:02,106
[Edward] She shouldn't have died.

141
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:04,817
She was one of my Marias.

142
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:08,196
[Alice sobbing shakily, whimpering]

143
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,864
I didn't want to kill her, but I had to!

144
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:10,865
[Alice breathes sharply]

145
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:15,912
- [unsettling music continues]
- [wind rustling]

146
00:08:28,966 --> 00:08:33,262
[unsettling music continues]

147
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:34,347
[Christina] <i>Heart?</i>

148
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:37,058
[Edward] <i>Yes, Heart?</i>

149
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:39,894
[Christina] <i>Have you heard</i>
<i>about what happened to Louisa?</i>

150
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:42,980
<i>Why?</i>

151
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:44,899
<i>What happened?</i>

152
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:46,484
[Christina] <i>She was murdered.</i>

153
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:48,819
- [dramatic music stings]
<i>- She's dead!</i> [sobbing]

154
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:51,656
- [unsettling music continues]
- [young Louisa sobs]

155
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:52,740
<i>- No!</i>
- [knife slashes]

156
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:54,742
<i>I'll go to Alice.</i>

157
00:08:54,825 --> 00:08:57,995
[Christina] <i>Who could</i>
<i>be so heartless to do that?!</i>

158
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:01,707
[sinister music playing]

159
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:02,708
- [pants]
- [Edward] <i>Stop!</i>

160
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:04,919
- [young Louisa] <i>Ah! Let me go!</i>
- [watch thuds]

161
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:08,881
[sinister music continues]

162
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:10,341
[Christina] <i>I'm coming with you.</i>

163
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,178
[thuds]

164
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:19,809
[sinister music continues]

165
00:09:22,770 --> 00:09:23,938
[breathes shakily]

166
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,279
What happened there?

167
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:33,155
Get changed.

168
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,407
Let's go.

169
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,118
Alice is already waiting for us.

170
00:09:38,035 --> 00:09:39,161
Let's get going.

171
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:43,749
[sinister music continues]

172
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:46,168
[dramatic music stings]

173
00:09:51,132 --> 00:09:53,634
[Edward] <i>I should've thrown</i>
<i>away that watch a long time ago.</i>

174
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,851
<i>If Althea hadn't seen it…</i>

175
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:07,106
[sinister music continues]

176
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,152
[thuds]

177
00:10:17,199 --> 00:10:20,161
[Beth] <i>When the police</i>
<i>found a watch in Edong's things</i>

178
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:21,579
<i>that looked like Louisa's,</i>

179
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:24,957
<i>even though it wasn't really hers,</i>
<i>we said</i>…

180
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,501
<i>Actually, I said,</i>
<i>that it belonged to Louisa.</i>

181
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,670
[Edward] <i>Heart, I'm home!</i>

182
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:32,673
[sinister music continues]

183
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:35,926
[Edward] <i>Then she wouldn't</i>
<i>be in the hospital right now.</i>

184
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,596
She got close to my heart.

185
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:41,474
Just like you…

186
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:43,684
my Marias.

187
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:47,104
Don't call us that, you motherfucker!

188
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:48,314
You bastard!

189
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:50,691
You don't own us!

190
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:53,778
You killed Louisa, you bastard!

191
00:10:53,861 --> 00:10:54,862
Fuck you!

192
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:56,864
Fuck you. [sobs]

193
00:10:56,947 --> 00:10:58,574
Fuck you! [inhales sharply]

194
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:00,409
Do you think you're some saint?

195
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:04,038
You acted like you cared
but it was really you who took her!

196
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:07,041
You didn't just ruined our lives!

197
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:10,211
You also ruined
the lives of Edong and Lucas!

198
00:11:10,878 --> 00:11:13,756
We all suffered because of you!

199
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:15,716
[all whimpering, sobbing]

200
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,259
[Erica] And for what?

201
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,637
To protect your wickedness?

202
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:23,057
[Edward] Why do
you look at me like that, Erica?

203
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:24,600
Don't you know me?

204
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:26,352
[Alice sniffles]

205
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:30,272
My father and your father…

206
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:32,608
were both violent.

207
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:35,236
They're both sick in the head!

208
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,823
Alice told me so.

209
00:11:39,657 --> 00:11:42,326
So we're not different, Attorney.

210
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,788
We're both made in the same mold!

211
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:49,458
And you, Mel…

212
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:54,422
Don't you like men who are also crazy?

213
00:11:55,714 --> 00:11:56,757
Just like me.

214
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:02,346
[Edward chuckles]

215
00:12:02,430 --> 00:12:04,140
And we're just the same, Beth!

216
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:05,474
You're just the bottom of the barrel!

217
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,394
You're craving for a father,

218
00:12:08,978 --> 00:12:10,187
who will love

219
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,523
and accept you!

220
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:16,277
But I understand you.

221
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:19,196
The four of you! Huh?

222
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,115
[whimpers]

223
00:12:21,198 --> 00:12:24,034
I've always been there for you, haven't I?

224
00:12:25,327 --> 00:12:27,621
I was your go-to person, right?

225
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,417
Have you forgotten that?!

226
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:33,586
Have you forgotten that?!

227
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:38,674
- [tense music playing]
- [crying]

228
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:48,267
[wailing]

229
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,937
Don't you dare compare yourself to us!

230
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,315
You don't know us!

231
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:56,442
You used us.

232
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:59,570
You used us the way
you used Auntie Christina!

233
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:02,406
All to just cover for your sins!

234
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,824
You monster!

235
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,743
I already told you.

236
00:13:06,243 --> 00:13:08,954
Don't talk to me like that!

237
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,831
You manipulated us!

238
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:13,375
You misled us about Kyle

239
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:15,961
just so you could keep lying to us!

240
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:19,798
You killed and abused those kids!

241
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:22,301
They were kids! My God!

242
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:23,594
You disgusting pig!

243
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:25,554
Don't talk to me like that!

244
00:13:26,805 --> 00:13:27,932
- Alice!
- Huh?!

245
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:30,184
- [whimpering]
- [music intensifies]

246
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:31,644
[grunting]

247
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:32,728
[flesh squelches]

248
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:34,230
[groaning]

249
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:35,981
[Mel] Let's go, let's go Alice!

250
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,817
- [Edward grunts]
- [Alice screaming]

251
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:40,903
[Erica] Let go of her!

252
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:43,531
- [Beth screams] Erica!
- [Erica grunts]

253
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:44,949
- [Edward grunts]
- [Alice breathes heavily]

254
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:46,158
- [Erica grunts]
- [Beth whimpers]

255
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,201
- [blow lands]
- [Edward grunts]

256
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,285
[thuds]

257
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:49,537
Let's go! Let's go!

258
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:50,621
- Come on!
- [Mel] Let's go!

259
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:51,622
[Beth] Come on!

260
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,499
- [Edward grunts]
- [Beth, Erica screams]

261
00:13:53,582 --> 00:13:55,084
[Beth] Let us go!

262
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,669
[grunting, whimpering]

263
00:13:56,752 --> 00:14:02,424
[tense music playing]

264
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:12,601
[music fades]

265
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:13,978
[gunshot]

266
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:15,771
[body thud]

267
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:24,738
[foreboding music playing]

268
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:26,991
- [gasps]
- [Alice breath quivers]

269
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:28,492
[Alice whimpers]

270
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:33,956
[whimpers, breathes heavily]

271
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:37,793
- [Mel breathes heavily]
- [Alice whimpers]

272
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:42,256
[foreboding music intensifies]

273
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:57,730
[foreboding music continues]

274
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:07,656
[Alice whimpers]

275
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:18,292
[foreboding music continues]

276
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:20,377
That serves him right.

277
00:15:23,505 --> 00:15:25,799
The first time I saw him,

278
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:29,678
I knew he was a monster too.

279
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:33,474
[foreboding music crescendos]

280
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,267
[Mel sobs quietly]

281
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:41,523
[ominous music playing]

282
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,651
Finally…

283
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:47,363
[inhales] …it is all complete.

284
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:53,035
Who should I kill first?

285
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:55,412
[Erica] Edong,

286
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:58,123
it was Edward who killed Louisa.

287
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:00,292
[breath quivers]

288
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:03,087
We already know the truth.

289
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:06,507
We can finally clear your name.

290
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:10,302
[inhales]

291
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:14,098
[moans]

292
00:16:14,682 --> 00:16:16,850
This is your husband's gun.

293
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:20,521
- I should go after you first.
- [Erica gasps] No, please.

294
00:16:20,604 --> 00:16:22,106
No, please, Edong!

295
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:23,691
[cries, sobs] Edong, please, no!

296
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:25,442
- No, no… [cries]
- Edong, just shoot me instead!

297
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,195
- [Mel] No-- No!
- Let them go.

298
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:30,114
- No! Erica, please. No!
- No! My god! What are you doing?!

299
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:31,407
Just shoot me!

300
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,408
Stop it, Erica.

301
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:34,284
- No. Please…
- Please, no.

302
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:36,161
I should have spoken up before, but…

303
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,789
But, I couldn't.

304
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:40,082
[crying]

305
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,250
[Erica sobs] You're right…

306
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:43,585
I'm fake.

307
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:45,713
[sobbing]

308
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:47,589
I'm worthless!

309
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,216
[Erica crying, sobbing]

310
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:50,759
So just kill me instead!

311
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,261
Kill me!

312
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:54,013
- No, please!
- Stop it, Erica!

313
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,723
No one else should die!

314
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,725
- [sobbing]
- [tense music playing]

315
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:01,603
One more step, attorney…

316
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:06,525
I'll blow your head off.

317
00:17:06,608 --> 00:17:08,318
- [whimpers]
- [breath quivers]

318
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:10,362
[sobs]

319
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,823
[Beth] Edong… [sobs]

320
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:15,200
Edong, I'm sorry.

321
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:16,910
[Beth crying]

322
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:18,078
I'm sorry! [sobs]

323
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:19,830
After everything that happened,

324
00:17:19,913 --> 00:17:22,541
this is what I should
have said a long time ago.

325
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:24,585
This is what
you should've heard a long time ago.

326
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:27,546
- [Edong snickering]
- Edong, forgive us.

327
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:29,631
[sobs] Forgive me.

328
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,717
- [laughing manically]
- It's not your fault,

329
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,135
it's mine!

330
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:34,928
- [manic laughing continues]
- [crying, sobbing]

331
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:37,848
- Fuck you!
- [whimpers]

332
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:41,226
I don't need your sorry!

333
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,979
[Edong shrieks]

334
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,981
It's too late.

335
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,275
[hisses, exhales]

336
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,986
We're way past that!

337
00:17:51,695 --> 00:17:53,655
- [Edong laughs]
- Edong, it's not too late.

338
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:56,825
- [Edong wheezes, groans]
- It's not.

339
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:58,744
You can still stop this…

340
00:17:58,827 --> 00:17:59,787
[sobs]

341
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:02,206
…and choose a life with Lucas.

342
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,291
[whimpering, sobbing]

343
00:18:04,374 --> 00:18:07,086
He can't afford to lose you too, Edong.

344
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:10,047
- [Edong] Don't…
- You already lost your mother.

345
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:12,424
- you drag…
- He can't afford--

346
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:14,635
- …my family into this!
- [gasps, whimpers]

347
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:15,719
[breathes heavily]

348
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,137
Shut the hell up!

349
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:19,348
- [all whimpering]
- [panicked breaths]

350
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:22,351
You all destroyed my family!

351
00:18:22,434 --> 00:18:23,393
[Lucas] Edong, stop! [echoes]

352
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,104
[music fades]

353
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:26,730
[Erica] When I was 17,

354
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,690
I put an innocent man to prison.

355
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:34,947
That is, without contest,

356
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:37,324
the worst thing that I've ever done.

357
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:40,119
I blamed the system,

358
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:42,913
the corrupt police officials,

359
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:46,708
the people
that wielded justice irresponsibly.

360
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,378
But, the truth is…

361
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:52,548
the person I blamed the most was myself.

362
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:55,592
- Because I kept silent.
- [poignant music playing]

363
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:57,928
Because I let fear prevail.

364
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,764
Because I chose the easier truth…

365
00:19:01,723 --> 00:19:03,267
instead of the real one.

366
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:06,895
I carried that guilt for 14 years.

367
00:19:08,021 --> 00:19:09,940
I carried it into law school,

368
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,401
into my practice,

369
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:17,990
even into every court
room win that didn't feel like a win.

370
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:22,536
Because no matter what case I win,

371
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:26,540
there's always
a voice in my head whispering,

372
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,543
"Why didn't you speak up back then?"

373
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,838
It took me a long time

374
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,424
to understand something important.

375
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:41,430
There are times when
justice seems out of reach.

376
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,599
But even so,

377
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:48,270
we shouldn't stop raising our voices.

378
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:51,064
Like me,

379
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:52,858
we will fail…

380
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:55,152
spectacularly.

381
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:57,571
We are not always brave.

382
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:02,034
We don't always win.

383
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,620
- [Lucas] Edong, stop!
- [poignant music intensifies]

384
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:06,788
[women sobbing]

385
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:10,542
- [Lucas] <i>Edong! Edong! Stop!</i>
- [music becomes somber]

386
00:20:11,668 --> 00:20:12,794
[Mel] What?

387
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:15,088
[Lucas] Stop this, please!

388
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:18,967
I should've seen
the hell you went through!

389
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:24,014
I should've seen that you needed help!

390
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:27,351
But I believed what I wanted to believe…

391
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:29,686
[somber music continues]

392
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:31,313
…that you were okay,

393
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:34,274
that you had fixed yourself inside prison.

394
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:39,029
Because that was easiest for me to accept!

395
00:20:40,113 --> 00:20:41,657
That was my mistake!

396
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,701
But, brother…

397
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,121
it's not too late.

398
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,707
[somber music continues]

399
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:52,584
I can still help you.

400
00:20:53,835 --> 00:20:58,507
We can still rebuild our lives.

401
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:01,843
[somber music fades]

402
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:04,221
He said we're no different.

403
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:05,681
[melancholic music playing]

404
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:07,182
Crisanto?

405
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:09,893
Am I just like him, bro?

406
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:13,563
[breathing shakily]

407
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:14,856
No…

408
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,277
You're not like him, brother!

409
00:21:21,822 --> 00:21:27,286
- [music becomes sinister]
- [breath hisses]

410
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:31,039
You're lying!

411
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:32,499
[Edong inhales sharply]

412
00:21:32,582 --> 00:21:34,209
[sinister music swells]

413
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:35,585
[Lucas] Please, Edong!

414
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:36,837
[women whimpering]

415
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,046
[Beth] No…

416
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:43,552
[music becomes suspenseful]

417
00:21:54,438 --> 00:21:55,772
[tense music sting]

418
00:21:56,815 --> 00:21:57,649
[gunshot echoes]

419
00:21:58,317 --> 00:21:59,443
[music ends]

420
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:03,071
[ominous music playing]

421
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:06,575
[both grunting]

422
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:07,909
- [gunshot]
- [women scream]

423
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,328
[women whimpering]

424
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,830
<i>[reporter]</i>
<i>A painful truth has come to light.</i>

425
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:15,250
<i>That he didn't commit</i>
<i>the murder of Louisa Soria.</i>

426
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:17,210
[Alice]<i> If it wasn't for Edong,</i>
<i>we wouldn't have known</i>

427
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:19,671
<i>the things we were hiding from each other.</i>

428
00:22:19,755 --> 00:22:21,631
<i>He will never be a complete villain to me.</i>

429
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:23,675
<i>But I still wouldn't want</i>
<i>to go through all that again.</i>

430
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:24,926
<i>No way in hell.</i>

431
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:30,682
[eerie whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]
